and access sensitive information collected by the Board. I think the 
Board’s  reputation  is  as  strong  as  it  is  because  it  has,  over  the 
years, been able to gather all the facts, and to protect the informa-
tion until the facts lead to the resolution of the investigation. When 
I was at the Labor Department, we put a great priority on improv-
